About the Enterprise SaaS Team
We believe your work is shaped by the tools you use. We provide a suite that integrates messaging, video conferencing, schedule management, collaborative documents, cloud storage, email, and workflow applications to provide a seamless collaboration experience on all your devices.   We are part of Enterprise Services team that create the next-gen suite of collaboration and productivity tools which is used by many companies internationally. We are a highly technical and skilled team that empowers one another to learn and strive. Want to build new features and improve existing features on our product? Want to solve the most challenging and complex technical problems? You can help to build the next-gen enterprise collaboration platform that will shape and transform the future of workplace collaboration. We are looking for talented individuals to join us in 2021 - people who want to inspire creativity and co-create the future with us. Responsibilities
... Participate in the development of third-party application ecosystem and the Helpdesk feature
- Participate in the R&D of multiple complex modules and systems, and manage the entire life cycle of related R&D work, including product discussion, feature analysis, documentation, design coding, testing and maintenance, and result tracking

1. Final year or recent graduate with a background in Software Development, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems or a related technical discipline;
2. Experience in Software Development and coding in a general purpose programming language is a plus;
